                                         ETokenType packageSeparator,

                                         CLikeVariableUseExtractor useExtractor)
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        language - the concrete language of this parser
        validIdentifiers - all token types that can be used as identifiers
        primitiveTypeTokens - all token types that can be part of a primitive type
        additionalTypeTokens - token types besides primitive ones that can be used to specify a type
        packageSeparator - the token that is used to separate packages/scopes/namespaces
        packageSeparatorText - the string representation of the package separator

        Collects type name tokens from a primitive type within a variable declaration. The assumption is that a primitive type can consists of multiple primitiveTypeTokens like "unsigned long long" in C++.

      • collectTokenFromTypePart

        protected int collectTokenFromTypePart(java.util.List<IToken> tokens,
                                       int endIndex,
                                       TypeNameTokenCollection typeName)
        Collects a type name token from a part of a type name within a variable declaration. A part is the name of a namespace/package or the type's name itself. E.g. the complete typename std::vector<int> consists of the parts std and vector. Generic/templated parts are skipped.

      • getVariableTokensFromForLikeTokens

        public java.util.List<IToken> getVariableTokensFromForLikeTokens(java.util.List<IToken> forLikeTokens,
                                                                 ETokenType endToken)
        Returns all variable declaration tokens within a for-like statement. For-like statements are for loops and similar constructs like using and catch statements in Cs. The given end token type specifies the token where the variable declaration tokens end.

      • getVariableUsesFromTokens

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getVariableUsesFromTokens(java.util.List<IToken> tokens,
                                                                   java.lang.String variableName,
                                                                   boolean isField,
                                                                   boolean isShadowed)
        Returns all token indices from the given tokens that are uses of the variable with the given name. The heuristic is to look for all occurrences of the variable name in the given tokens. An occurrence is considered as variable usage, if the following token is not in validIdentifiers. Those token types are set from the subclass for a concrete language. Internally a CLikeVariableUseExtractor is used.
        Parameters:
        isField - if the variable is a field
        isShadowed - if the variable is a field and shadowed by another local variable

                                                                    java.lang.String variableName,
                                                                    boolean isField,
                                                                    boolean isShadowed)
        Returns all token indices from the given tokens that read the value of the variable with the given name.
        Parameters:

        isShadowed - if the variable is a field and shadowed by another local variable
